{
  "texts": [
    "• FL (federated learning): a privacy-preserving machine learning approach where decentralized data sources collaboratively train a shared model without exchanging raw data.",
    "• IoT (internet of things): a system of interconnected physical devices that collect and transmit data via the internet to enhance decision-making and automation.",
    "• IoMT (internet of medical things): a subset of IoT encompassing medical devices and health systems connected to networks for real-time data exchange and monitoring.",
    "• ML (machine learning): a branch of AI that enables systems to learn patterns from data and make predictions or decisions without being explicitly programmed.",
    "• DL (deep learning): a subset of ML that uses multilayered neural networks to analyze complex patterns and highdimensional data."
  ]
}